On Jun 14, 2007, at 12:04 PM, Jorge Almeida wrote:

> I'm missing something about Perl's regexp:
>
>   1 #!/usr/bin/perl -w
>   2 use strict;
>   3 my $s=;
>   4 $s=~s/\D*//;
>   5 $s=~s/\D*//;
>   6 print "$s\n";
>
> When input is 'a123b', I get '123b', but I expected '123'.

   s/\D+//g;

-- fxn


